artwork_title: Warren Avenue at 23rd Street, Detroit, Michigan, October 1993, Joel Sternfeld
metadata:
Artist
Joel Sternfeld
Title
Warren Avenue at 23rd Street, Detroit, Michigan
Origin
United States
Date
Made 1993
Medium
Chromogenic print, from the series "On This Site: Landscape in Memoriam," edition 1 of 7
Inscriptions
Inscribed and signed recto, on mount, lower right, below image, in black ink: "Warren Avenue at 23rd Street, Detroit Michigan. (October 1993) / 1/7 Joel Sternfeld"; unmarked verso Malice Green dropped off a friend in front of this suspected crack house right before he was stopped by two police officers. After Green was asked to produce his driver’s license and registration, a struggle ensued and the officers beat him to death with three-pound flashlights. The beating continued even after Green had been handcuffed and an ambulance had been flagged down. Larry Nevers was found guilty of second-degree murder and sentenced to twelve to twenty-five years in prison. Walter Budzyn, convicted of the same crime, was given eight to eighteen years. From the series, On This Site: Landscape in Memoriam
Dimensions
47.3 × 59.8 cm (image/paper); 71.2 × 82.7 cm (mount)
Credit Line
Acquired from the Center for Documentary Studies, Duke University, through an Anonymous Gift
Reference Number
1997.276
